Rating: 3
Very enjoyable recipe all around: fun prep, easy to cook, great tasting. I followed most of the reviewers tips: halve the recipe except the spices, add two stalks celery, omit the cloves, add a pinch of oregano, use 14.5 oz can diced tomatoes with jalapeno plus 8 fl. oz. Guiness Extra Stout plus 1 cup broth for liquid, substitute 1/2 tsp red pepper flakes for the cayenne. I used a 4-pack of chicken thighs bone-in but skinned and trimmed of fat. Also 8 to 10 shrimp cut into three chunks each, plus 3 or 4 thick asparagus stalks snapped into chunks, plus 5 or 6 sliced green onions --- these last three added on top at the end, for about 5 minutes. Used basmati rice and did NOT stir, as someone suggested (for me, that makes the rice mushy). Also added one large jalapeno --seeded, trimmed & chopped -- to the celery, onion, bell pepper & parsley mix. I used 1 tsp each of New Mexico mild chili and an India chili. Will probably cut back red pepper flakes by a smidge next time; but after thinking uh-oh at first taste, the heat was fine and did not distract from the lovely blend of flavors. Hat tip to the reviewer who suggested asparagus: I'll double that next time. I heated the liquids in the microwave to near boiling before adding, which is a tip from my favorite Spanish rice recipe. Initial cook time was 20 minutes, then a scant 5 more for the shrimp & veggie toppings, then remove from heat and let sit for 10 minutes. Served this for two while watching a movie; it was so good, we each made two trips back to the kitchen! Roughly one-third was left over.

