I've made this one several times with a few adaptations. It is huge so unless you are like us and love great leftovers cut it in half. I use 3lb. of boneless skinless breast and thighs. Brown the sausage in a separate skillet while sautéing the onion & garlic in the olive oil, then brown the chicken in the same skillet. We like spicy so I increase the caynne to 1 tsp. and I add a can of diced tomatoes in juice (it isn't too much liquid for the full amt. of rice but if halving you may need to decrease the liquid. I also use part red and yellow bell peppers for better flavor and color. I also add them and the parsley at the same time as the rice to help retain some color and texutre. The combo of chili pdwr,thyme and clove is fantastic. 30 min is plenty of time for the rice-more and it will be overcooked and mushy. One of my favorite Epicurious recipes.

