Rating: 3
I made this for a Mardi Gras party and it was a huge hit - a few people said it was the best they'd ever had! I substitued boneless chicken breasts, which I marinated in cajun sauce and olive oil, sauteed, and then stirred in at the very end. I also substitued 16 oz. canned tomato sauce for one cup chicken broth, and I used jerk flavored spicy sausage. When it was done cooking it was a bit bland, but after a hefty dose of salt and pepper was perfect. Pretty spicy!

